This paper deals with the security analysis of separation kernels, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a specification development method and reviews the source code of ARINC SK implementations, which involves software engineering (cs.SE), operating systems (cs.OS), programming languages (cs.PL), and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR, followed by cs.SE, cs.OS, cs.PL, and cs.LO.
